        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued May 6 at 3:13AM CDT until May 6 at 4:00AM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 313 AM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Knickerbocker,
moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Golf ball size hail and 60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...People and animals outdoors will be injured. Expect hail
damage to roofs, siding, windows, and vehicles. Expect wind
damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

This severe storm will be near...
Twin Buttes Reservoir, Lake Nasworthy, Goodfellow Air Force Base,
and San Angelo around 320 AM CDT.
Wall around 325 AM CDT.
Veribest around 335 AM CDT.
Vancourt and Mereta around 340 AM CDT.

Other locations impacted by this severe thunderstorm include Harriet
and Us-67 Near The Irion-Tom Green County Line.
</description>
        <instruction>A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 400 AM CDT for west central
Texas.

For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
